    "We only study n = 100 in an initial effort to provide evidence of an evaluation bias (due to the relatively small test set), and take 20 repeated subsamples instead of 50.",
    "While n = 100 is quite small, benchmarks such as LegalBench (Guha et al., 2024) have test data in this range.",
    "And the analysis transparently exposes variance.",
